WEBVTT

00:00.083 --> 00:01.500
[Joe]
<i>Previously on</i> Jonas LA...

00:01.583 --> 00:02.667
[Nick] Oh!

00:02.750 --> 00:04.000
Nick!

00:04.500 --> 00:06.041
What has gotten into you?

00:06.125 --> 00:10.208
You just seem different this summer.
Good different.

00:10.291 --> 00:11.500
[laughs]

00:11.583 --> 00:13.291
Well, I talked to my director

00:13.417 --> 00:15.542
about who should play
my love interest in <i>Forever April,</i>

00:15.625 --> 00:18.041
<i>and she wants a Joe from Jonas type.</i>

00:18.125 --> 00:20.500
There's a roomful of me's in there
and I'm freaking out right now.

00:20.583 --> 00:22.583
-Action.
-I'm a ghost.

00:22.667 --> 00:24.750
Ghosts can't love.

00:24.834 --> 00:27.959
If we never try, then we'll
never know what could have been.

00:28.041 --> 00:29.917
-And cut.
-I got the part!

00:31.542 --> 00:34.375
-Here you go, man. I made you breakfast.
-Wow. Thanks, dude.

00:34.458 --> 00:36.291
No problem.
Feeling good? Feeling loose?

00:36.375 --> 00:38.333
Feeling awesome.
I'm going to be in a movie today.

00:38.417 --> 00:40.083
Not just any movie!

00:40.166 --> 00:42.083
From the best-selling novel,
<i>Forever April,</i>

00:42.166 --> 00:45.959
comes the major motion picture event,
starring my brother, Joe.

00:46.041 --> 00:48.250
[chuckles]
Dude, no sausage.

00:48.333 --> 00:51.834
In a world with no sausage,
one man--

00:51.917 --> 00:53.750
Tells his brother
to stop talking like that.

00:53.834 --> 00:57.375
Oh, yeah. Sorry.
Hey, let's practice your lines.

00:57.458 --> 01:00.959
Kevin, we've been practicing all weekend.
I'm pretty solid.

01:01.041 --> 01:03.625
OK, then you wouldn't care
if I did this...

01:03.709 --> 01:08.291
Scene 36, interior, high school gymnasium,
your character, Dade, is alone.

01:08.375 --> 01:10.166
The ghost April appears. She says,

01:10.250 --> 01:12.792
[high-pitched]
"Dade, you're not safe here.

01:12.875 --> 01:16.250
-you have to go."
-"I'm not going anywhere without you."

01:16.333 --> 01:18.333
-Nailed it!
-See? Solid.

01:18.417 --> 01:22.000
-Now do it backwards.
-You without anywhere going not I'm.

01:22.083 --> 01:23.709
You are going to be a great actor.

01:23.792 --> 01:26.041
And you are going to be a great director.
Director Kevin?

01:26.125 --> 01:27.959
-Yes, actor Joe?
-What time is it?

01:28.041 --> 01:31.667
-Seven-thirty.
-And what time do I have to be on set?

01:33.083 --> 01:35.083
-Seven-thirty.
-So, we should probably...

01:39.083 --> 01:40.750
-[theme music playing]
-♪ <i>Yeah! ♪</i>

01:41.709 --> 01:43.083
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

01:43.625 --> 01:45.500
<i>♪ I was sitting at home ♪</i>

01:45.583 --> 01:48.834
<i>♪ Watching TV all alone ♪</i>

01:48.917 --> 01:51.291
<i>♪ So tired of routines ♪</i>

01:51.375 --> 01:54.500
<i>♪ The day goes on and on ♪</i>

01:54.583 --> 01:56.542
<i>♪ So I pick up the phone ♪</i>

01:56.625 --> 02:00.208
<i>♪ Call everyone I know ♪</i>

02:00.291 --> 02:02.041
<i>♪ I say there's gonna be a party ♪</i>

02:02.125 --> 02:06.083
<i>♪ Hit the music, here we go, yeah ♪</i>

02:06.166 --> 02:09.250
<i>♪ You gotta live to party</i>
<i>Bust your move ♪</i>

02:09.333 --> 02:12.000
<i>♪ Everybody's in the groove ♪</i>

02:12.083 --> 02:14.709
<i>♪ Tell the DJ to play our song ♪</i>

02:14.792 --> 02:17.333
<i>♪ Are you ready to rock and roll? ♪</i>

02:17.417 --> 02:20.125
<i>♪ Gotta live to party</i>
<i>Bust your move ♪</i>

02:20.208 --> 02:23.041
<i>♪ Everybody's in the groove ♪</i>

02:23.125 --> 02:25.500
<i>♪ Live to ♪</i>

02:25.583 --> 02:27.917
<i>♪ Party! ♪</i>

02:30.417 --> 02:31.709
[horn honking]

02:35.250 --> 02:37.208
According to this, the set should be...

02:37.291 --> 02:39.875
over there.
Or over there.

02:39.959 --> 02:42.750
Dude, you're the director.
Which direction are we going?

02:42.834 --> 02:45.625
Relax, OK? We're a little bit lost,
we're a little bit late...

02:45.709 --> 02:48.917
Look at this place!
We are not in Jersey anymore.

02:49.000 --> 02:53.250
Kevin, I was supposed to be
in makeup, like, yesterday.

02:53.333 --> 02:55.125
[laughs]
You have to wear makeup.

02:55.208 --> 02:56.709
-[chuckles]
-[sighs]

02:57.917 --> 02:59.834
There it is.
Come on.

03:00.458 --> 03:03.000
[Kevin] Chill. We're in Hollywood,
nothing starts on time.

03:06.834 --> 03:10.000
You're late. Who said you could be late
to a Mona Klein set?

03:10.959 --> 03:12.792
-He did.
-Hi, Ms. Klein, I'm Kevin.

03:12.875 --> 03:14.750
I'm Joe's brother.
Also a director!

03:14.834 --> 03:17.709
-Well, aspiring. But I'm just a big fan.
-Zip it!

03:17.792 --> 03:20.083
You, sit down while I decide
how I'm gonna punish you.

03:20.166 --> 03:21.750
-It won't happen again.
-No kidding.

03:21.834 --> 03:23.709
This movie is my big comeback.

03:23.792 --> 03:25.917
After <i>Soccer Squirrels 2:</i>
<i>Nuts in New York,</i>

03:26.000 --> 03:27.792
-they said I'd never work again.
-I loved that movie.

03:27.875 --> 03:29.500
Well, the critics didn't.

03:29.583 --> 03:32.709
But <i>Forever April</i> is going to
get me back to where I belong.

03:32.792 --> 03:36.208
Unless you mess it up,
so be on time!

03:36.834 --> 03:40.000
Mona, my yoga class ran over.
Sorry I'm late.

03:40.083 --> 03:43.500
Oh, sweetie, what's a few minutes?
Take all the time that you need.

03:43.583 --> 03:46.250
Oh... the face on that one.

03:49.834 --> 03:50.917
[door shuts]

03:51.583 --> 03:53.625
Vanessa, how did you get away with that?

03:53.709 --> 03:55.792
Mona totally chewed me out
for being late.

03:55.875 --> 03:59.458
I have exited Vanessa.
I am now April.

03:59.542 --> 04:01.792
-What?
-Dade, is that you?

04:01.875 --> 04:04.458
Joe, this is a technique
some actors use to prepare.

04:04.542 --> 04:07.625
They become the character
even when the cameras aren't rolling.

04:07.709 --> 04:09.750
Dade, am I visible?

04:09.834 --> 04:11.834
-Play along.
-Yes.

04:11.917 --> 04:13.417
April, I can see you.

04:13.500 --> 04:17.291
You're the only mortal
I can communicate with and I need...

04:17.375 --> 04:20.542
-something.
-What is it, April?

04:20.625 --> 04:23.291
A bagel, lightly toasted
with the middle scooped out.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.542
I'll get it.

04:29.291 --> 04:31.041
-[Nick] All right, you strum.
-[Macy] OK.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.583
G-G-G-G, C-C...

04:35.667 --> 04:38.208
-We're doing it.
-We are shredding "Twinkle, Twinkle."

04:38.291 --> 04:40.750
I think guitar should always be
a two-person instrument.

04:40.834 --> 04:43.583
Depends on the two people.

04:45.792 --> 04:47.291
Maybe you should try it on your own.

04:47.375 --> 04:49.917
Oh. Um...

04:50.000 --> 04:50.917
OK.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.166
[hip hop music playing]
Hey... Whoo!

04:53.250 --> 04:54.333
how you doing?

04:54.417 --> 04:57.000
Hey, DZ, we're kind of
in the middle of something.

04:57.083 --> 04:59.875
Introducing DZ, AKA: Lady Candy,
as in candy for ladies,

04:59.959 --> 05:02.208
not as in, you know,
I'm a lady named Candy.

05:02.291 --> 05:03.959
I get it.
I don't want to get it, but I get it.

05:04.041 --> 05:06.375
Ladies and gentlemen,
I have a big date tonight.

05:06.458 --> 05:08.166
And, oh, this is real velour,

05:08.250 --> 05:10.583
so if you were to, uh, you know,
rate my look

05:10.667 --> 05:12.417
on a scale of jamming to slamming?

05:13.875 --> 05:16.458
-Um...
-You hate it.

05:17.083 --> 05:18.792
Hug me.

05:18.875 --> 05:21.000
Ow!
Uh, DZ, you're hair's really sharp.

05:21.083 --> 05:22.834
Oh, sorry.
I must have over-gelled.

05:22.917 --> 05:25.500
OK, DZ, back away from the Jonas.

05:25.583 --> 05:29.000
Whatever is going on,
it can't be that bad.

05:29.083 --> 05:33.750
The... the truth is,
I'm not the player you think I am.

05:35.125 --> 05:37.583
And I've never been on a date before.
There, I said it.

05:37.667 --> 05:40.667
-That is a huge shock.
-[softly] Yeah.

05:40.750 --> 05:43.500
-But it's gonna be OK.
-It's not gonna be OK. All right?

05:43.583 --> 05:45.792
I'm meeting Andrea tonight.
My threads are busted,

05:45.875 --> 05:50.208
-and this bling is giving me a rash.
-OK, I can help you.

05:50.291 --> 05:52.417
But you're gonna have
to do it my way, understand?

05:52.500 --> 05:55.125
-Yeah, where do we start?
-Follow me. Let's go.

06:02.625 --> 06:03.917
OK, Aunt Lisa, I'm ready.

06:04.000 --> 06:06.834
Oh, thanks for letting me
practice on you, Stella-bell.

06:06.917 --> 06:09.166
You know, I think massage
is my true calling.

06:09.250 --> 06:11.917
I do.
I know I said that about acting.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.375
And candle-making.

06:14.458 --> 06:17.709
-And landscaping.
-Hey, it's a free massage. I'm in.

06:17.792 --> 06:20.417
Oh, I am going to be charging
a pretty penny for this,

06:20.500 --> 06:22.792
once I get into massage school, so...

06:22.875 --> 06:23.917
-Get in?
-Mm-hmm.

06:24.000 --> 06:27.125
I thought...
I thought you were already... you know?

06:27.208 --> 06:31.000
-Oh, no. Let's begin.
-OK.

06:31.083 --> 06:32.917
-[clears throat]
-[knuckles crack]

06:38.000 --> 06:40.417
Who's a good girl?
Do you like that?

06:40.500 --> 06:42.792
Hm?
[giggles]

06:42.875 --> 06:44.667
-Hey, Lisa?
-Yeah?

06:44.750 --> 06:50.750
Is there any chance that before me
you've only massaged, say, a cat?

06:51.834 --> 06:54.000
Oh, yeah.
Oh, there's a chance.

06:59.041 --> 07:04.000
OK, in this scene, Dade goes to the house
where April's spirit lives.

07:04.083 --> 07:06.083
-Cool.
-Joe, I need you to play this

07:06.166 --> 07:08.417
-scared, yet tough.
-Got it.

07:08.500 --> 07:10.750
Confident, yet vulnerable.

07:10.834 --> 07:13.959
-Really?
-I want big, big emotions

07:14.041 --> 07:16.917
played in a very, very small way.

07:17.000 --> 07:18.959
-OK, on that one how do I--
-Camera rolling!

07:19.041 --> 07:20.291
-Wait!
-What?

07:20.375 --> 07:22.250
-Aren't we gonna rehearse?
-Rehearse?

07:22.333 --> 07:23.625
What is this, your high school play?

07:23.709 --> 07:26.792
This is the big time.
You're a professional actor,

07:26.875 --> 07:28.667
and every minute on this set costs money.

07:28.750 --> 07:30.875
This conversation?
A million dollars.

07:30.959 --> 07:33.375
Saying "a million dollars"?
$27,000.

07:33.458 --> 07:35.000
[Kevin]
Excuse me, guys, is everything OK?

07:35.083 --> 07:37.375
-Who are you?
-I'm Joe's brother. We've actually met.

07:37.458 --> 07:39.291
[groans]
Family. No, thanks.

07:39.375 --> 07:41.792
This is why I have birds. Shoo!

07:41.875 --> 07:43.583
Cue effects.

07:43.667 --> 07:44.917
[fan whirring]

07:47.417 --> 07:48.500
Cue music.

07:50.000 --> 07:52.875
-[ballad playing]
-And action!

07:53.625 --> 07:55.709
[Vanessa]
Why do you keep coming here?

07:55.792 --> 07:58.500
Nothing good ever happens
in this terrible place.

07:58.583 --> 08:02.959
-I just need to be close to you.
-No, you need to forget me.

08:03.041 --> 08:06.083
Try, Dade.
Pretend I never existed.

08:06.166 --> 08:09.625
But I can feel you all around.
In the silence I hear...

08:10.625 --> 08:12.000
Line!

08:12.083 --> 08:14.500
-The sound of!
-Cut!

08:18.750 --> 08:21.166
-Do you not know your lines?
-I did not.

08:21.250 --> 08:23.834
I mean, I did.
I'm just nervous.

08:23.917 --> 08:26.333
I'm not paying for nervous.
Go again.

08:26.417 --> 08:29.625
Cue effects.
Music!

08:29.709 --> 08:33.333
-[ballad playing]
-And action!

08:33.417 --> 08:35.709
[Vanessa]
Why do you keep coming here?

08:35.792 --> 08:39.333
Nothing good ever happens
in this terrible place.

08:44.083 --> 08:46.583
-Uh...
-Cut!

08:48.792 --> 08:51.333
What's the deal?
You know, everybody take five.

08:52.500 --> 08:55.875
You get your act together
or you're gonna see my dark side. OK?

08:57.083 --> 08:58.500
It gets darker?

08:59.041 --> 09:00.500
[shudders]

09:00.583 --> 09:02.625
-[DZ] Ow!
-[Macy] Quit squirming.

09:02.709 --> 09:05.917
-Ow!
-What did you put in here, glue?

09:06.000 --> 09:08.166
I don't know.
It was my grandfather's toupee cream.

09:08.458 --> 09:11.500
[sighs]
I'm gonna need a bigger comb.

09:25.625 --> 09:27.125
So, do we like?

09:27.417 --> 09:30.750
-No.
-Oh, boy.

09:31.959 --> 09:33.083
[Kevin]
You're doing great, bro.

09:33.166 --> 09:34.750
Stop saying that.
I'm a mess.

09:34.834 --> 09:37.291
-Just try and relax.
-Maybe I just don't belong here.

09:37.375 --> 09:39.333
What does this chair say?

09:39.709 --> 09:41.834
-It says "Joe."
-Yes, exactly.

09:41.917 --> 09:44.208
"Joe," not Lou, not Ed, but Joe.

09:44.291 --> 09:46.875
They wouldn't give you a chair with your
name on it if you didn't belong here.

09:46.959 --> 09:50.000
-Who's Ed?
-I'm trying to make a point.

09:50.083 --> 09:51.750
You're fine saying the lines with just me.

09:51.834 --> 09:54.166
Well, you don't have a dark side.
Mona freaks me out.

09:54.250 --> 09:56.750
-What if she fires me?
-I won't let that happen.

09:56.875 --> 09:59.959
We gotta go much tighter on Joe.
Throw a 75 on, OK?

10:00.041 --> 10:01.875
-[man] Gotcha.
-Hi, Mona.

10:03.250 --> 10:05.500
You just pop up all over the place,
don't you?

10:05.583 --> 10:08.208
Yeah. I think I figured out
what Joe's problem is.

10:08.291 --> 10:10.709
-Oh, do tell.
-It's you.

10:11.709 --> 10:12.792
I'm the problem?

10:12.875 --> 10:15.667
Well, yeah, you have a way of
saying things that are scary and mean.

10:15.750 --> 10:18.333
Joe, on the other hand,
likes things that are soft and nice.

10:18.417 --> 10:21.125
-Oh, does he?
-If you could give him rewards,

10:21.208 --> 10:23.250
maybe like treats or snacks,
that could really help him.

10:23.333 --> 10:25.792
Fascinating. You know,
I have a different approach.

10:25.875 --> 10:27.709
-Oh, what's that?
-Security!

10:28.458 --> 10:30.625
-No, that's--
-Get him off my set.

10:30.709 --> 10:33.667
No, I'm OK. Hey... We're fine.
[chuckles]

10:33.750 --> 10:35.291
Bye-bye.

10:35.375 --> 10:38.291
-Wait, what happened?
-We talked. You're all good.

10:38.333 --> 10:42.041
-[screams]
<i>-What?</i> No.

10:44.291 --> 10:46.917
Come on, guys, I've gotta get back to set.
My brother needs me.

10:47.000 --> 10:49.208
[grunts]
Guys, come on!

10:50.041 --> 10:52.417
-[beeps]
-Joe, talk to me.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.333
Dude, why did Mona kick you off the set?

10:54.417 --> 10:57.041
Things were said.
It's not important. So, how you doing?

10:57.125 --> 10:59.875
I am freaking out.
You need to get back here.

10:59.959 --> 11:01.959
[Mona]
Picture's up. Where's Joe?

11:02.041 --> 11:04.917
-She coming.
-Joe? Joe!

11:07.834 --> 11:08.750
[tires screeching]

11:09.750 --> 11:10.709
I don't think so.

11:13.041 --> 11:15.417
Listen, my brother really needs me.
He's back there on set.

11:15.500 --> 11:19.917
And I need a three-hour foot massage,
followed by a four-hour foot massage.

11:20.041 --> 11:22.166
I think we're both gonna be disappointed.

11:25.041 --> 11:27.000
[piano chords playing]

11:27.083 --> 11:31.000
May I present the new
and majorly-improved DZ?

11:31.083 --> 11:32.959
Wow, DZ, is that really you?

11:33.041 --> 11:35.750
Holla! [chuckles]
Back up the cool bus.

11:35.834 --> 11:37.625
[imitates engine starting]

11:38.333 --> 11:40.375
Beep, beep, beep, beep.

11:40.458 --> 11:41.375
[beatboxes]

11:41.458 --> 11:42.750
Stop.

11:42.834 --> 11:45.291
-Whoo.
-Yep, still you.

11:45.583 --> 11:48.083
I forgot he still talks.
It really kills the look.

11:48.166 --> 11:50.583
Wait, wait, you guys think
I need more than this?

11:50.667 --> 11:55.000
Girls love a good dresser,
but the clothes are just the packaging.

11:55.083 --> 11:57.083
There's so much more
that we like in a guy.

11:57.166 --> 11:59.625
Uh-oh, Macy's about to
lay some knowledge on us, DZ.

11:59.709 --> 12:01.667
Oh, well, DZ's all ears.

12:01.709 --> 12:04.583
-Well, we like a guy with confidence.
-I reek of confidence.

12:04.667 --> 12:07.417
That's my body spray,
Confidence by Stone Stevens.

12:07.500 --> 12:09.542
Yeah, there's such a thing
as too much confidence.

12:11.125 --> 12:14.583
-Uh, we like it when you listen to us.
-Oh, like I said, all ears.

12:14.667 --> 12:16.875
-But still have your own opinions.
-Totally.

12:16.959 --> 12:19.333
-[whispers] About what?
-Oh, I know!

12:19.417 --> 12:21.041
We like a guy who can make us laugh...

12:21.125 --> 12:23.875
Well, I got this off the back
of a gum wrapper:

12:23.959 --> 12:26.875
Why don't seagulls fly by the bay?

12:28.625 --> 12:32.083
Because then they'd be called "bay-gulls."
[laughs]

12:32.166 --> 12:35.458
-Stop it.
-But not with jokes. I really hate jokes.

12:35.875 --> 12:38.291
[clears throat]
Come on, flying baked goods?

12:38.375 --> 12:40.417
DZ, just listen.

12:40.500 --> 12:43.583
Care about your family and your friends.

12:43.667 --> 12:45.959
And show the world
you have a beautiful spirit.

12:46.041 --> 12:48.166
And always, always chew
with your mouth closed.

12:48.250 --> 12:49.750
-Got it?
-Got it.

12:49.834 --> 12:51.625
Anything else?

12:51.709 --> 12:56.959
One more thing:
if you like a girl, you should tell her,

12:57.041 --> 13:00.500
so she's not confused
by the messages you're sending.

13:00.583 --> 13:03.792
Got it, processed.
Outskis. See ya.

13:05.917 --> 13:07.583
-You deserve a medal.
-Thank you.

13:07.667 --> 13:12.667
-[door opens, closes]
-So, anything I said surprise you at all?

13:12.750 --> 13:14.041
Or...?

13:14.417 --> 13:17.917
Jokes. I didn't know
they were a deal breaker.

13:23.333 --> 13:25.125
[exhales]

13:27.083 --> 13:29.250
Officer Evie, may I call you Evie?

13:29.333 --> 13:31.667
There has to be someone
in here you want to talk to.

13:31.750 --> 13:33.000
Matt Damon?

13:33.875 --> 13:35.500
Usher?
Kesha?

13:35.583 --> 13:38.959
I don't play like that.
You got Will Smith in there?

13:39.041 --> 13:40.959
-No.
-Oh, well!

13:41.041 --> 13:43.125
I guess we're stuck.

13:45.583 --> 13:47.625
Oh, no, that boy didn't just do that.

13:48.959 --> 13:51.917
[groans]
I had to wear the big heels today.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.000
Boy!

13:53.875 --> 13:55.959
[Vanessa]
Why do you keep coming here?

13:56.041 --> 13:58.959
Nothing good ever happens
in this terrible place.

13:59.041 --> 14:03.166
-I just need to be close to you.
-No, you need to forget me.

14:04.041 --> 14:06.875
Try, Dade.
Pretend I never existed.

14:07.750 --> 14:10.041
Around all you feel can I but.

14:12.000 --> 14:14.333
[groans]
I just said it backwards.

14:14.417 --> 14:16.000
